P* designates an internucleotide linkage to a preceding monomer, or a 3'-terminal group;
R4* and R2* together designate a biradical consisting of 1-4 groups/atoms selected from -C(RaRb)-, -C(Ra)=C(Rb)-, -C(Ra)=N-, -O-, -Si(Ra)2-, -S-, -SO2-, -N(Ra)-, and >C=Z,
